    <text transform="translate(457 3943.8)" style="white-space:pre" y="-3415.5" fill="#333" font-family="Roboto" font-size="32" font-weight="300" letter-spacing=".5">
  <tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan>The Document Object Model (DOM) allows you to access elements of a web page and enable interaction with </tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan>the page by adding and removing elements, changing the order, content and attributes of elements, and even </tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan>altering how they are styled.</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan>In this chapter, weâ€™ll cover the following topics:</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan> â€¢ Introduction to the DOM</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan> â€¢ Getting elements â€• </tspan><tspan class="mono">getElementById</tspan><tspan> , </tspan><tspan class="mono">getElementsByClassName</tspan><tspan> , </tspan><tspan class="mono">getElementsByTagName</tspan><tspan> , </tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan> </tspan><tspan class="mono">querySelector</tspan><tspan> and </tspan><tspan class="mono">querySelectorAll</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan> â€¢ Navigating the DOM</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan> â€¢ Getting and setting an elementâ€™s attributes</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan> â€¢ Updating the DOM by creating dynamic markup</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan> â€¢ Changing the CSS of an element</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan> â€¢ Our project â€• we&apos;ll dynamically insert each question into the HTML</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-288.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan>
    </text>

    <text style="white-space:pre" transform="translate(1959.5 3847.6)" font-family="Roboto" font-size="32" font-weight="300" letter-spacing=".5">
      <tspan x="-1790.8" y="-1757">The Document Object Model, or DOM for short, represents an HTML document as a network of connected </tspan><tspan x="-1790.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan>nodes that form a tree-like structure.</tspan><tspan x="-1790.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-1790.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan>The DOM treats everything on a web page as a node. HTML tags, the text inside these tags, even the attributes </tspan><tspan x="-1790.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan>of a tag are all nodes. The HTML tag is the root node, and every other part of the document is a child node of</tspan><tspan x="-1790.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan> this.</tspan><tspan x="-1790.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan x="-1790.8" dy="1.8em">â€‹</tspan><tspan>Take the following piece of HTML as an example:</tspan>
    </text>

    <text transform="translate(278.3 5638.6)" style="white-space:pre" fill="#333" font-family="Roboto" font-size="73" letter-spacing="-2.5">
      <tspan x="-109.5" y="-3801.4">The Document Object Model</tspan><tspan x="-109.5" dy="1em">â€‹</tspan>
    </text>
    <text transform="translate(278.2 5767.9)" style="white-space:pre" fill="#333" font-family="Roboto" font-size="49" letter-spacing="-2.5">
      <tspan x="-109.5" y="-3801.4">What is the DOM</tspan><tspan x="-109.5" dy="1em">â€‹</tspan>
    </text>

    <path fill="#f3f0ee" d="M168.7 2597.8h1578v88.7h-1578z"/>
    <text style="white-space:pre" x="455.3" y="3949.8" fill="#333" class="mono" font-size="32">
      <tspan x="195.7" y="2653.5" fill="#8596bb" word-spacing="0">&lt;</tspan><tspan word-spacing="0">p </tspan><tspan fill="#408fb5" word-spacing="0">class</tspan><tspan word-spacing="0">=</tspan><tspan fill="#709b1f" word-spacing="0">&apos;warning&apos;</tspan><tspan fill="#47629d" word-spacing="0">&gt;</tspan><tspan word-spacing="0">Something has gone </tspan><tspan fill="#677dad" word-spacing="0">&lt;</tspan><tspan word-spacing="0">em</tspan><tspan fill="#6379aa" word-spacing="0">&gt;</tspan><tspan word-spacing="0">very</tspan><tspan fill="#47629d" word-spacing="0">&lt;/</tspan><tspan word-spacing="0">em</tspan><tspan fill="#47629d" word-spacing="0">&gt;</tspan><tspan word-spacing="0"> wrong!</tspan><tspan fill="#46629d" word-spacing="0">&lt;/</tspan><tspan word-spacing="0">p</tspan><tspan fill="#405c9a" word-spacing="0">&gt;</tspan>
    </text>
    <text style="white-space:pre" x="168.7" y="2791.9" fill="#333" font-family="Roboto" font-size="32" font-weight="300" letter-spacing=".5">This can be represented as the tree diagram shown below.
